def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    if key is None:
        key = group_axis

    gpr = key

    groupings = []
    exclusions = []

    for i, level in enumerate([level]):
        name = None

        if key not in obj.columns:
            raise KeyError(f"{key} not found in columns")

        if is_categorical_dtype(obj[key]) and len(obj[key]) != obj.shape[axis]:
            raise ValueError(
                (
                    "Length of grouper ({len_gpr}) and axis ({len_axis})"
                    " must be the same length".format(len_gpr=len(obj[key]), len_axis=obj.shape[axis])
                )
            )

        ping = (
            Grouping(
                group_axis,
                obj[key],
                obj=obj,
                name=name,
                level=level,
                sort=sort,
                observed=observed,
                in_axis=True,
            )
        )

        groupings.append(ping)

    grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)

    return grouper, exclusions, obj
